text: 1) Acetaminophen is great for pain/fever. May cause issues with liver function 2) Ibuprofen is also great for pain/fever. May be some bleeding risk. 3) Dextromethorphan is okay for cough. Not the best, not the worst. May have some interactions with antidepressants.  4) Doxylamine can help with sleep and histamine related issues (runny nose) may cause drowsiness.  At no point did I ever claim the above chemicals were not effective for their indications. They do not help treat the cold or flu, which are viral infections. Nothing listed above has antiviral activity.  Expensive combinations of these medications are not cost effective and are also worthless for treating a viral infection. They are a waste of money.  Zinc is the best we have OTC to treat the common cold and potentially the flu. This recommendation comes from several sources, most pertinent is the AAFP. If you disagree with that, take it up with them, not me.   5) Phenylephrine is not effective as  a decongestant. The FDA has issues a warning about it.  6) Guaifenesin is also worthless at thinning secretions. There is more data supporting this claim than the opposite.  Stop claiming this is medical misinformation and the board should take my license away. Everything I said in this video was 100% accurate or well within reason for a medical professional to claim based on available data.
